Industrial Area deputy Officer Commanding Station Proctus Walucho has died. Walucho succumbed to Pulmonary Embolism while undergoing treatment at Nairobi West Hospital in Nairobi on Saturday. The incident was reported to Makadara police station on OB Number: 3/17/10/2020 at 3.00 pm as ‘death of police officer’. “Please be informed that Walucho was suddenly taken ill on 16/10/2020 at around 1600 hours and was admitted at NRB West Hospital where he was diagnosed with pulmonary embolism,” reads the police report in part. More to follow